<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcbc25b5b-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s41707"><num value="41707">§ 41707.</num><heading> Incorporating contract terms into written instrument</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">To the extent the Secretary of Transportation prescribes by regulation, an air carrier may incorporate by reference in a ticket or written instrument any term of the contract for providing interstate air transportation.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idcbc25b5c-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/272/s1/e">Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)</ref>, <date date="1994-07-05">July 5, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/1141">108 Stat. 1141</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
